  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Global Fund Transitional Funding Mechanism</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CRS Niger is one of two principal recipients for a Global Fund Transitional Funding Mechanism (TFM) project to tackle malaria in Niger, through the Conseil National de Coordination Multisectorielle de Lutte contre le Sida, la Tuberculose et le Paludisme (CCM Niger).</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project incorporates the distribution of more than 2 million long-lasting insecticide-treated nets (LLINs) in the Dosso and Tillab&#xE9;ri regions, as well as 4 million malaria diagnostic kits (RDTs) and 1.5 million doses of medication (ACTs) nationwide, accompanied by awareness-raising through radio campaigns.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Women, children under five, those suffering from malaria</narrative>
  </description>
